metadata: (info { (description "This game, which consists of a board of two rows of four holes, sometimes with extra holes, has been found as graffiti in medieval Al-Andalus (Spain). It has been thought to be a type of mancala game.") (rules "2x4 board. Two extra holes, to the side. ") (source "DLP evidence.") (id "1791") (version "1.3.14") (classification "board/sow/two rows/reconstruction/pending") (credit "Eric Piette") (origin "This game was played in Spain, from around 800 to 1099.") } ) (graphics { (board Style Mancala) }) (recon { (concept "Sow" True) })
